nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
1) 'LOADERS' group:
    - Configure Image dimensions (before upscale) and Upscale Multiplier

2) 'SUBJECT' groups:
    - Configure Subject Dimensions and Offset - location of the top-left corner of 
      the subject in relation to the full image. Keep in mind that y increases 
      downwards
    - Feel free to use this Desmos graph for help: https://www.desmos.com/calculator/ycedaiekqt

3) 'FIRST PASS SAMPLER SETTINGS' group:
    - Adjust settings for samplers in the first pass

All dimensions should be divisible by 64. And this applies to the second pass as well. For Upscale Multiplier, this means that it will be difficult to find a non-integer value that will work. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- The black reroute nodes act as switches that allow you to configure the generation process further or enable extra functions like ControlNets

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 ControlNets:
   To enable: 
     1)attach a ControlNet Loader to the purple reroute node
     2)change the strength of ApplyControlnet (it's zero by default)
     3)switch on with the black reroute node switch

   To disable revert step #3

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - To add a subject, copy a Subject group structure on top of the existing chain and connect everything in the same manner

 - To disable a subject:
   - Set 'strength' in 'SubjectSize/Location - 1Pass' (ORANGE) and 'SubjectSize/Location - 2Pass' (YELLOW) to 0
   - rewire the 'LatentComposite_DF' (PURPLE) node chain on the right side of subject groups so that the one in the disabled subject is omitted
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - Some overlapping of subject areas is fine, but with too much overlap the subjects may get distorted or become one
